# Real-Time Automotive Dashboard Using CAN Protocol

## ?? Project Overview
This project implements a real-time automotive dashboard using the CAN (Controller Area Network) protocol with ARM7 LPC2129 microcontroller. The system monitors and displays vehicle parameters such as speed, RPM, temperature, and fuel level.

## ?? Objectives
- Implement CAN communication using LPC2129
- Display real-time vehicle data on LCD
- Develop firmware using Embedded C
- Ensure reliable ECU communication

## ?? Hardware Components
- ARM7 LPC2129
- CAN Transceiver (MCP2551)
- LCD Display
- Power Supply Unit

## ?? Software Tools
- Keil uVision
- Embedded C
- Flash Magic

